<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">   [QUOTE]Originally posted by Viper:
[i]I would be nice to disable the Windows button. Especially when it's so close to the ALT key[/i][/QUOTE]
Well only if it's optional, I like to get back to Windows every now and then

   [QUOTE]Originally posted by Viper:
[i]I was fighting in the dungeons, postponing the use of a health potion, and I was almost out of health.... just 2 more skeletons to go; I thought I'd manage them without getting killed and I did BUT... I levelled during when I slayed the first one and.... *tadaa* full health restored. I sthat normal?[/i][/QUOTE]
As far as I know: Yes

   [QUOTE]Originally posted by Viper:
[i]Sometimes I had to click several times before he'd use them. eg.: the book near the beehive (had to click it 3 times) and the hatcj in the abandoned house (somewhere in the right upper area of the town), had to click that 3 times as well. for the rest some doors wouldn't open the first time or he wouldn't read books lying on the floor the first time I clicked them; he just went to those objects.[/i][/QUOTE]
I experienced the same but I think the trigger positions are a bit off. I found out that if I just click at the lower part of the object, it always works.

  [QUOTE]Originally posted by Viper:
[i]It would be nice to be able to zoom a little bit out. and the viewrange should be a bit larger. (I don't know how the game looks in 1024*768 so it could be good in that mode)[/i][/QUOTE]
It has pros and cons. The biggest con is that it gets all very small and that you might miss objects.


  [QUOTE]Originally posted by Moriendor:
[i]6) When you play as a warrior it would be cool if the 'Way of the Warrior' would be displayed as the default page when you hit the "Skills" button (in the demo, the 'Way of the Wizard/Mage' is shown first). Same goes for wizard and survivor, of course. Just display the way fitting to the char after the player hits the "Skills" button.[/i][/QUOTE]
Are you sure? I thought it showed the last skill screen you used before, but I'm not sure anymore  :)

